CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 15, 1960, pg. 3 reads: " "Welcome Jack" - "Mr. Pennsylvania," Governor David L. Lawrence, gives Senator John Kennedy a real Golden Triangle welcome before the Democratic nominee for President spoke to the thousands of fans at Gateway Center."
TitMainTitle: President John F. Kennedy shaking hands with Pennsylvania Governor David L. Lawrence, surrounded by crowd including Florence Reizenstein and Joseph Barr, during Kennedy - Johnson campaign, Gateway Center
